cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.MM

The paper proposes a deep learning technique for automatic glaucoma screening from fundus images. This involves image analysis and classification, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. The use of deep learning also suggests the involvement of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper involves image processing and feature extraction, which are relevant to the information retrieval (cs.IR) and multimedia (cs.MM) sub-categories.
